  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesised that endocardial stem cells implantation following after
      percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) could reduce the scar formation and increase reverse
      remodeling in patients with primary acute myocardial infarction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
