    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>PCI and Stem Cells or Placebo injections</intervention_name>
    <description>Conventional percutaneous coronary intervention after acute myocardial infarction. Harvest of bone marrow from iliac crest. Mesenchymal autologous stem cells preparation (7-10 days after PCI). LV mapping with Noga system (7-10 days after PCI). Randomization 1:1. Stem Cells or placebo implantation.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Group 1 (PCI+SC implantation)</arm_group_label>
