  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with acute Q-wave myocardial infarction after thrombolitic therapy during
             6-36 hours from the onsent of signs

          -  Oclusion or significant stenosis of infarct-related left anterior descending artery
             (LAD)

          -  Left ventricle ejection fraction (LVEF) &lt; 50% measured by Echo

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Thrombolysis of pyrrolase or streptokinase

          -  Surgical unsignificant stenosis of LAD

          -  Indications for CABG

          -  Cardiogenic shock

          -  Uncontrolled hypertension

          -  Thrombocytopenia

          -  Ongoing bleeding

          -  Anemia &lt; 100 g/l

          -  Oncology

          -  Patients, who required anticoagulation therapy at the time of inclusion

          -  Obesity, BMI&gt;40

          -  Severe comorbidities

          -  Unwillingness to participate
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
